                <p class="title">How should I care for my pillow... </p>
                <p class="p1"><em>I</em><em>f it’s screen printed?</em></p>
                <p class="p1">The fabric is machine washable in cold water on the gentle cycle and should be dried on low or hung to dry. Both the printed and plain linen used on these designs are not washed prior to sewing but have similar shrink rates. We generally suggest hanging to dry. Colors may fade slightly with washing and direct sunlight. Over time, linen does tend to relax a bit, so if your cover is feeling a little big for your insert we suggest drying it on low heat. High heat can cause the cover to shrink too much.<span class="Apple-converted-space">  </span>Iron on medium heat as necessary. If your pillow has a metallic back, please see below.</p>
